Please note that not all us longtime Star Wars fans hate TLJ or even the prequels completely and unconditionally. If I get whiny about anything in Star Wars is that there is not enough common soldier type heroes and too much Jedi acrobatics. But that's just me, I absolutely LOVED TLJ and I tried my hardest to STILL like BF2 but EA just shat on it a lil' TOO much even for me. Not enough people getting angry over THAT if you ask me. I'm 27 and close to a die-hard fan, and I know plenty of people who like Star Wars casually that both make fun of it and like it for their own reasons at the same time (take your memes and your good moments like the Battle of Hoth). I think the fact that I'm here writing up a big reply speaks for itself, but while there are tons of shitty fans in ANY fandom (Star Wars, Undertale, Doctor Who, Steven Universe, Star Trek, Harry Potter or what have you) not all fans are shitty, and in fact probably outnumber the bad in any scenario. The bad are just more vocal, the casuals and/or other longtime fans like me are just not as much...and you know what that's okay I guess, the more vocal the losers get the more I realize that it's probably just a fad to hate something, liking something genuine can be lifetime~
